  • Forgery-Uttering [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.38(2).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Antonio L Williams in court, in custody, with attorney Timothy T. Kay.   Shawn N Woller appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant enters a no contest plea as to count 2. Court imposed the following sentence:

  The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

IMPOSED SENTENCE of: 

3 YEARS IMPRISONMENT (CREDIT - 260 days)
  -  18 MONTH(S) OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
  -  18 MONTH(S) OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION; sentence to run concurrent

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:  
*Attend Criminal Thinking counseling
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain employment and/or combination of schooling 
*No contact with:  Target, victim/witnesses or co-actors
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done.
 
RESTITUTION:  $0 

COURT COSTS:  $268.00 (to be paid as a condition of extended supervision);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $250.00 (to be paid as a condition of extended supervision);

Defendant is eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant is not eligible for Substance Abuse Program.

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
